Rating based on comparison with restaurants available nearby:
(Overall: 2.6, Rating given to closest whole number)

Food: 3, Nothing special. Portions are average too. In general Chinese food is oily. This place is no different.

Decor: 2.2. The owners seem to be practical people and haven't really invested in making their place of business more presentable.

Comfort: 2.5 Not the best seating, nor does the seating density allow for elbow or leg movement.

Service: 2.5, Nothing notable here except that I didn't leave with good impressions.

Price: 3, Generally aligns with the norm. 

Sanitation: 2.5, There's a sort of grimy feeling when you enter the cafe. It's although as if there is an overhang of oil in the very air that you breathe in there. This can be improved immensely.

Personal Commentary:
I once had breakfast with my partner here. Suffice to say we were both quite unimpressed with the lack of quality of the food. It was oily, slightly cold and not very appetizing. For course you might argue, "what is one to expect for 30 HKD?", but then we've had much better at alternative locations close by.
